<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-info">
  <h4>Picking your weather model</h4>
  <p>
    Before you can run your simulation, you need to identify the model by which you will
    simulate weather.  You can choose form all the weather models that have been uploaded
    into the SmartFarm site, or you can <%= link_to 'create your own', new_weather_path %>
    and then come back to create your simulation.
  </p>
</div>

 <div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="panel panel-primary">
      <div class="panel-heading">
        <h4 class="panel-title">Weather Model to Use</h4>
      </div>
      <div id="selected-weather" class="panel-body">
        <%= render @simulation.weather if @simulation.weather %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

   <div class="col-md-8">
      <h4>
        Farms
        <div class="btn-group">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-success">My Weather Models</button>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-default">All Weather Models</button>
        </div>
      </h4>
      <div id="unselected-weather">
        <%= render Weather.all %>
      </div>
  </div>
</div>

